ACT:
 Kerala General Sales Tax Act 1963-Section 39(4)-Scope of-Appellate Tribunal-If possesses jurisdiction or power to enhance assessment in the absence of an appeal or cross- objection by one of the parties.
 Section 39(4) (a) (i) of the Kerala General Sales Tax Act 1963 provides that in disposing of an appeal, the Appellate Tribunal, may, after giving the parties a reasonable opportunity of being heard either in person or by a representative confirm, reduce, enhance or annul the assessment or penalty or both.
 
